personalInfo.education: University of North Florida (2012, Public Relations)

tourBios.exmtStatus: Conditional - Finished T108 at 2015 Web.com Tour Qualifying Tournament
tourBios.carHigh: 2014: Finished T64 at Web.com Tour Q-School in December...Competed in 15 events on the NGA Tour and won the Kandy Waters Memorial Classic in a playoff over Casey Clendenon and Ken Looper.
tourBios.otherCarHigh: Finished fourth in stroke play at the 2006 U.S. Amateur Public Links before falling in the first round of match play in a sudden-death playoff...Named an Atlantic Sun All-Freshman as a freshman at the University of North Florida in 2006-07...Finished with five top-10 finishes in three years at UNF.
tourBios.personal: Attended Seabreeze High School in Daytona Beach, Fla...Entrance song on the first tee would be "Thunderstruck" by AC/DC...Favorite athlete is Dan Marino...Best sporting event attended was the Notre Dame-Stanford game in South Bend, Ind...Wants to be featured in Forbes because it will mean that he is successful...Favorite restaurant is Mellow Mushroom, and favorite pro team is the Jacksonville Jaguars...Favorite courses played are Pebble Beach and Diamond Creek, with bass fishing his biggest thrill outside golf...Would like to be a professional fisherman, if he weren't playing golf...Favorite entertainer is Hootie and the Blowfish and his favorite quote is "You can't change the direction of the wind, but you can adjust your sails."...Twitter name is @sirjamescarl.

dyn.dynResults: His best finish on the Web.com Tour was T36th in 2015 at the Chile Classic.
dyn.dynStats: He ranks T5th in Longest Drives on the Web.com Tour.
